{{Infobox company | company_name = Actifio | company_logo = | company_type = Private | company_slogan = | foundation = 2009 | location_city = [[Waltham, Massachusetts]] | key_people = Ash Ashutosh, [[Entrepreneur|founder]] and [[Chief executive officer|CEO]] | num_employees = | industry = [[Information Technology]], [[data backup]], [[big data]], [[business continuity]], [[disaster recovery]], [[data protection]], [[Computer data storage|data storage]] | revenue = | operating_income = | net_income = | homepage = http://actifio.com/ }} '''Actifio''' is an [[information technology]] and software company based in [[Waltham, Massachusetts]]. It produces software products for [[Computer data storage|data storage]], specifically a data protection product with integrated [[data backup]] and [[disaster recovery]] features.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.storage-switzerland.com/Blog/Entries/2010/9/10_Actifio_Briefing_Note.html|title=Actifio Briefing Note|date=January 2011}}</ref> Actifio launched in November 2010 at [[Tech Field Day]].
Actifio received much press<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fool.com/investing/general/2010/07/22/actifio-wants-to-virtualize-data-management.aspx|title=Actifio Wants to "Virtualize" Data Management|accessdate=January 2011|work=Motley Fool}}</ref> due to the presence of [[Entrepreneur|founder]] Ash Ashutosh, who had gained attention as chief technologist at [[HP]]'s [[HP StorageWorks|StorageWorks]] division. That company had acquired another Ashutosh startup, AppiQ.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.storagenewsletter.com/news/business/actifio-start-up|title=A Secret Storage Start-Up: ActiFio|accessdate=January 2011|work=Storage Newsletter}}</ref>
